    <section name="Add date to Documentttype">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to add a datefield to a documenttype.</span>

   <div class='screenshot'>
     <img src="../../../../images/inars/add_date_to_documenttype.png" alt='Add date to documenttype screenshot'/> 
     <p>
      Adding mandatory datefield sar:date_of_happening with caption 'Date of happening' 
      to documenttype `upcoming'.      
     </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    Open the <a href='./goto_documenttype_tab.html'>documenttype</a> for editing. 
    In the list of possible fields, 
    click on 'Date' (far right, almost at the top, 
    Below 'Text' and Above 'Boolean'). 
    A date field appears as part of the documenttype.
   </p>
   <ul>
    <li>
     <a href='./fieldcaption.html'>Define a caption for the new field</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
     Also <a href='./naming_a_field.html'>define a name</a> for it.
    </li>
    <li>
     And decide if it should be <a href='./mandatory_or_optional.html'>mandatory or optional</a>.
    </li>
   </ul>

